OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRyanair's Michael O'Leary  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwants 'practical'          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fimmigration approach       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Ryanair boss Michael O'Leary has urged 
OL,6, the UK government to take a more       
OL,7, "practical, common sense" approach to  
OL,8, post-Brexit policy, to allow more      
OL,9, workers from Europe to fill vacancies. 
OL,11,FMr O'Leary said he could hire people   
OL,12,Ffrom continental Europe for jobs that  
OL,13,Fhe cannot fill with British workers,   
OL,14,Fbut is unable to get visas for them.   
OL,16,FFacilitating such visas would help ease
OL,17,Fdisruption to air travel, he said.     
OL,19,FThe government said it wanted firms to 
OL,20,Finvest in workers from the UK.         
